<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4654475>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Male calling song structure of Yoyetta enigmatica sp. nov. illustrated in waveform plots, including: (A) typical repeated echemes (in flight); (B) expanded section from (A) showing the detailed structure of a single echeme. The final subfigure (C) is a spectrogram displaying song frequency. This specimen was recorded in the field at Dawson Springs, Mt Kaputar (30°17'S 150°10'E) by LWP." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4654475/files/figure.png" .
